history.content: Sorry that this is causing some stress. If any of you have questions about the course replacement option and whether it would be in your best interest to make use of it, please feel free to contact Prof. Elad Alon atelad@berkeley.edu.

I am a graduating senior for the Spring 2017, and I am looking at the alternatives list. All the course alternatives seemed kinda specialized since most of them are upper divs. For example, you have a bunch of BioE, CivE, Math upper divs, that I feel if I take I would be behind. EE16A is more of a intro course, so how do the alternatives match up. Having a hard time choosing what to do. Thanks
history.subject: Alternatives
